00015     /*
00016     states of the Mathmaking
00017 
00018     when a invite is sent the PvpChallengeInvite is created and the variable open is set to true
00019     If the sender cancels the invite the open is set to false
00020     If the receiver rejects the invite the open is set to false
00021 
00022     If the receiver accepts the invite the open is still open with the response object created, the response object has an open variable which is set to true
00023     if the sender or receiver cancels the response the open is set to false
00024 
00025     if the admin makes the game then the open var is still true but this time the GameState Model gets created
00026     */
00027 
00028     /*
00029         States of the actual battle
00030 
00031         Both users need to commit their attacks      The combatState model will be in the phase of Commitment untill both fo the user have committed and at least one has revealed
00032         Both users need to reveal their attacks      The combatState model will be in the phase of Reveal untill both of the users have revealed
00033 
00034         run the round (only one user needs to do this)
00035      */
00036 
00037     /*
00038      the queries only come back if the full models are present if any of the models are not the then the query will not return anything
00039         thats where we can use the graphql query in that case
00040     */
00041 
00042     /*
00043         Models that are used in this script:
00044         PvPChallengeInvite
00045         PvPChallengeResponse
00046         CombatState
00047         PvPCombatants
00048 
00049         here its mainly used to get the games states, we basically save everygame the user has ever been from the pvp challenge invite model, and from there start the query chain to check where the state is at currently
00050      */
